body: I've seen an improvement already when using GLM 4.7 and Kimi K2.5 after swapping endpoints. Would suggest merging to improve the experience for Synthetic.new users.

@greptileai thanks for the catch! Re-review?

(I'm curious if this comment will work to trigger a re-review)

<details>
<summary>Additional Comments (3)</summary>

**`docs/providers/synthetic.md`**
**Frontmatter summary mismatch**

The doc frontmatter still says `summary: "Use Synthetic's Anthropic-compatible API in OpenClaw"`, but the body now documents OpenAI-compatible endpoints and `openai-completions`. This will show incorrect information in the docs index/preview and is inconsistent with the rest of the page.

```suggestion
summary: "Use Synthetic's OpenAI-compatible API in OpenClaw"
```

**`docs/providers/synthetic.md`**
**Example uses old default model**

In the config example, `agents.defaults.model.primary` and `agents.defaults.models[...]` still reference `synthetic/hf:MiniMaxAI/MiniMax-M2.1`, but this PR changes the Synthetic default model to `synthetic/hf:moonshotai/Kimi-K2.5`. Copy/pasting the example will not match the documented “default model is set to” and may confuse users.

```suggestion
    defaults: {
      model: { primary: "synthetic/hf:moonshotai/Kimi-K2.5" },
      models: { "synthetic/hf:moonshotai/Kimi-K2.5": { alias: "Kimi K2.5" } },
    },
```

body: I presume there's no pricing difference between those two models?

@HenryLoenwind for subscribers, all models are priced the same: they're free with the price of the subscription. Currently we treat all models identically with respect to rate limits, i.e. Kimi K2.5 and MiniMax M2.1 contribute the same amount to subscriber rate limits.

(FWIW they're not priced identically for non-subscriber pay-per-token, but almost none of our traffic is pay-per-token; almost everyone prefers the subscription plans since they're more affordable.)
